<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 02 at 1:58AM CDT until May 02 at 2:30AM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Hutchinson County in the Panhandle of Texas...
West central Roberts County in the Panhandle of Texas...
* Until 230 AM CDT.
* At 158 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles east of
Stinnett, or 9 miles northeast of Borger, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Hail damage to vehicles is expected.
* Locations impacted include...
Borger.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
